      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The expansion of welfare programs has had a complex effect on labor participation, often creating a disincentive for work among certain demographics. Generous benefits can sometimes lead to a \"welfare trap,\" where the marginal benefit of taking a low-wage job is outweighed by the potential loss of aid. However, these programs also provide a crucial economic floor, allowing individuals to pursue education or caregiving without facing destitution. Ultimately, the impact depends heavily on the specific design and phase-out rules of each program.",
